Import and Tidy

  1. Read the gazetteer data as-is (all columns; no type conversion) into a gaz_raw tibble.
gaz_raw <-
  read_delim(
    "CA_Features_20180401.zip",
    delim = "|",
    col_types = cols(.default = col_character())
  )
gaz_raw
  1. Extract and rename the columns we want to keep into a gaz tibble.
gaz <-
  select(gaz_raw,
    id         = FEATURE_ID,
    name       = FEATURE_NAME,
    class      = FEATURE_CLASS,
    state      = STATE_ALPHA,
    county     = COUNTY_NAME,
    lat        = PRIM_LAT_DEC,
    lon        = PRIM_LONG_DEC,
    src_lat    = SOURCE_LAT_DEC,
    src_lon    = SOURCE_LONG_DEC,
    elev       = ELEV_IN_M,
    map        = MAP_NAME,
    created_on = DATE_CREATED,
    edited_on  = DATE_EDITED
  )
gaz
  1. Convert the gaz columns to the appropriate type. Convert any placeholders for unknown data to NA.
gaz$id         = parse_integer(gaz$id)
gaz$lat        = parse_double(gaz$lat, na = "0")
gaz$lon        = parse_double(gaz$lon, na = "0")
gaz$src_lat    = parse_double(gaz$src_lat)
gaz$src_lon    = parse_double(gaz$src_lon)
gaz$elev       = parse_integer(gaz$elev)
gaz$map        = parse_character(gaz$map, na = "Unknown")
gaz$created_on = parse_date(gaz$created_on, format = "%m/%d/%Y")
gaz$edited_on  = parse_date(gaz$edited_on, format = "%m/%d/%Y")
gaz

  1. Delete from gaz rows where:

    • the primary latitude or longitude are unknown
    • the feature is not in California
gaz <-
  filter(gaz,
    !is.na(lon) &
    !is.na(lat) &
    state == "CA"
  )
gaz

Analyze

  1. What is the most-frequently-occuring feature name?

original:

gaz %>%
  count(name) %>% 
  filter(n == max(n))

SQL:

query = "
  SELECT name, n
  FROM (
    SELECT name, COUNT(name) AS n
    FROM gaz
    GROUP BY name
  )
  WHERE n = (
    SELECT MAX(n)
    FROM (
      SELECT name, COUNT(name) AS n
      FROM gaz
      GROUP BY name
    )
  )
"
dbGetQuery(db, query)
  1. What is the least-frequently-occuring feature class?

original:

gaz %>%
  count(class) %>%
  filter(n == min(n))

SQL:

query = "
  SELECT class, n
  FROM (
    SELECT class, COUNT(class) AS n
    FROM gaz
    GROUP BY class
  )
  WHERE n = (
    SELECT MIN(n)
    FROM (
      SELECT class, COUNT(class) AS n
      FROM gaz
      GROUP BY class
    )
  )
"
dbGetQuery(db, query)
  1. What is the approximate center point of each county?

original:

gaz %>%
  group_by(county) %>%
  summarize(
    ctr_lon = (min(lon) + max(lon)) / 2,
    ctr_lat = (min(lat) + max(lat)) / 2
  )

SQL:

query = "
  SELECT county,
         ((min(lon) + max(lon)) / 2) as ctr_lon,
         ((min(lat) + max(lat)) / 2) as ctr_lat
  FROM gaz
  GROUP BY county
  ORDER BY county
"
dbGetQuery(db, query)

  1. (cont’d)

    1. Join the feature categories to the gazetteer and summarize categories by county.

original:

gaz %>%
  select(county, class) %>%
  filter(!is.na(county)) %>%
  left_join(categories, by = "class") %>%
  group_by(county) %>%
  count(category) %>%
  spread(key = category, value = n) %>%
  left_join(count(gaz, county), by = "county") %>%
  mutate(
    frac_manmade = manmade / n,
    frac_natural = natural / n
  ) %>%
  select(county, frac_manmade, frac_natural)

SQL:

query = "
  SELECT t1.county AS county,
         CAST(manmade AS REAL) / (manmade + natural) AS frac_manmade,
         CAST(natural AS REAL) / (manmade + natural) AS frac_natural
  FROM
    (
      SELECT county, COUNT() AS manmade
      FROM (
        SELECT county, category
        FROM   gaz JOIN categories
        ON     gaz.class = categories.class
        WHERE  category = 'manmade'
      )
      GROUP BY county
    ) AS t1
    JOIN
    (
      SELECT county, COUNT() AS natural
      FROM (
        SELECT county, category
        FROM   gaz JOIN categories
        ON     gaz.class = categories.class
        WHERE  category = 'natural'
      )
      GROUP BY county
    ) AS t2
    ON t1.county = t2.county
"
dbGetQuery(db, query)
